data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime — the sync-over-async opt-in has been fully removed.**

In EF Core 10, Cosmos DB sync I/O was unsupported by default but could be re-enabled. In EF Core 11, there is **no opt-in**; `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` always throw.

**Fix:** Convert everything to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to update all callers to `await` these methods and propagate `async` up the call chain. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
